label.value: increased rate of mitotic spindle elongation during prophase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic spindle elongation is increased during miotic prophase.

label.value: decreased rate of mitotic spindle elongation during prophase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic spindle elongation is decreased during prophase.

label.value: transient abrupt spindle length decrease at anaphase onset

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the spindle length decreases abruptly at anaphase onset.

definition.value: In PMID:24239120, this is likely due to interpolar microtubules being shorter than kinetochore microtubules, so cleavage of cohesin links leads to the shrinkage in length.

label.value: decreased mating efficiency during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A biological process phenotype in which the observed mating efficiency, as determined by counting zygotes, asci, and sometimes spores, is lower than normal after nitrogen removal.

label.value: normal mating efficiency during nitrogen stress

value.value: A biological process phenotype in which the observed mating efficiency, as determined by counting zygotes, asci, and sometimes spores, is normal (i.e. the same as in wild-type cells) during nitrogen limitation or poor nitrogen source.

label.value: increased spontaneous diploidization due to abolished sister chromatid separation

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterothallic haploid cells spontaneously form cells with diploid DNA content after failing chromosome segregation and  consequently nuclear division. The nucleus is displaced from the cell center by actin cables, preventing chromosome cut and leading to diploidisation.

label.value: abolished nuclear displacement from cell division site after abolished mitotic sister chromatid separation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterothallic haploid cells failing chromosome segregation and  consequently nuclear division fail to displace the nucleus from the septation site. This is normally mediated by actin cables.

label.value: cut with mitotic spindle microtubules protruding beyond spindle pole body

value.value: An inviable phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle after normal chromosome separation in which pushing forces exerted by microtubules protruding from the spindle pole bodies displace one of the daughter nuclei to the site of cytokinesis. The septum then physically divides that nucleus into two parts, giving rise to inviable daughter cell.

label.value: short-lived long mitotic spindle microtubules protruding beyond spindle pole body

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form mitotic spindle microtubules that are longer than normal, extend beyond the spindle pole body and are present transiently. The protruding spindle microtubules are surrounded by an extension of the nuclear envelope.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.value: These protrusions are short-lived and labelled by Mal3 (presumably plus ends)

label.value: increased rate of microtuble polymerization during vegetative growth

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers to the plus end of a microtubule occurs at a higher rate, or speed, than normal.

label.value: increased rate of interpolar microtubule polymerization during mitotic anaphase B

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed during mitotic anaphase B in which interpolar microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers to the plus end of a microtubule occurs at a higher rate, or speed, than normal.

label.value: decreased rate of interpolar microtubule polymerization during mitotic anaphase B

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed during mitotic anaphase B in which interpolar microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers to the plus end of a microtubule occurs at a lower rate, or speed, than normal.

label.value: increased rate of interpolar microtubule polymerization inside the mitotic nuclear membrane bridge

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed during mitotic anaphase B in which interpolar microtubule polymerization occurs at a higher rate, or speed, than normal for microtubules with their plus ends inside the nuclear membrane bridge formed during mitotic anaphase B.

definition.value: Microtubule growth speed is normally decreased when plus ends internalise in the nuclear membrane bridge, but this occurs to a lesser extent in this phenotype

label.value: abnormal distribution of interpolar microtubule rescue during anaphase B

value.value:
A cellular process phenotype observed during anaphase B in which the distribution of the positions of interpolar microtubule rescues is abnormal.
The positions of interpolar microtubule rescues are where the transitions from shrinkage to growth occur.

label.value: increased duration of interpolar microtubule growth events during anaphase B

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed during anaphase B in which the duration of interpolar microtubule growth events is longer.

label.value: abnormal homologous chromosome pairing during meiosis I prophase

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype in which homologous chromosome pairing during meiosis (synapsis) is abnormal during meiotic prophase I.

label.value: decreased homologous chromosome pairing during meiosis I prophase

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype in which homologous chromosome pairing during meiosis (synapsis) is decreased during meiotic prophase I.

label.value: increased number of microtubules per bundle during mitotic interphase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which cells contain interphase microtubule bundles with more microtubules than normal.

label.value: Increased microtubule overlap length in bundles during mitotic interphase:

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which cells contain interphase microtubule bundles with microtubule overlaps longer than normal.

label.value: abnormal interpolar microtubule length distribution during anaphase B

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the distribution of lengths of interpolar microtubules in the mitotic spindle is abnormal during anaphase B.

label.value: single microtubule bundle with aster-like microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which all detectable microtubules are present in a single bundle and are not normally crosslinked, resulting in an aster-like organisation. See PMID:15068790.

label.value: microtubule bundles detached from the nuclear envelope

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed during mitotic interphase in which some microtubule bundles are not anchored to the nuclear membrane. See PMID:15068790

label.value: abolished eMTOC disassembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which equatorial microtubule organizing center (eMTOC) disassembly does not take place after cell division.

label.value: early eMTOC assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which equatorial microtubule organizing center (eMTOC) assembly occurs earlier than normal. eMTOC assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an equatorial microtubule organizing center.

label.value: decreased protein localization to interphase microtubule bundle overlap

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during mitotic interphase in which the localization of a protein to the microtubule overlap of cytoplasmic microtubule bundles is decreased.

label.value: decreased rate of spindle elongation during meiotic anaphase B

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the rate, or speed, of meiotic spindle elongation is decreased during anaphase B.

label.value: long spindle microtubules protruding beyond spindle pole body during meiosis I

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in meiosis I in which cells form meotic spindle microtubules that are longer than normal, and extend beyond the spindle pole body. The protruding spindle microtubules are surrounded by an extension of the nuclear envelope.

label.value: abolished nuclear congression during mating

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which karyogamy involved in conjugation with cellular fusion does not occur because the nuclei fail to come in physical contact.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for isoleucine

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize isoleucine, and therefore requires isoleucine in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for valine

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize valine, and therefore requires leucine in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is decreased during metaphase.

label.value: decreased protein localization to pericentromeric region during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during the first meiotic nuclear division in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the pericentromeric regions is decreased.

label.value: normal meiotic sister chromatid cohesion protection during meiotic anaphase I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the cohesion protection during anaphase of the first meiotic nuclear division is normal.

label.value: abolished protein localization to old cell tip during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the old cell tip does not occur during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: thin actin cables

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in mitotic interphase in which cells form actin cables that are thinner than normal. This is evidence by lower actin fluorescence signal and is likely due to the presence of fewer actin filaments than normal.

label.value: monopolar actin cortical patch localization to new end

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cortical patches are localized to only the new end of a cell following cell division.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to interphase microtubule bundle

value.value: A cell phenotype observed during mitotic interphase in which the localization of a protein to interphase microtubule bundles is abnormal.

label.value: abolished protein localization to spindle pole body during karyogamy

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the spindle pole body is abolished during karyogamy.

label.value: increased sensitivity to chemical in stationary phase

value.value: A phenotype in which cells show increased sensitivity to a chemical when the cell population is in stationary phase. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of that chemical that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to menadione in stationary phase

value.value: A phenotype in which cells show increased sensitivity to menadione when the cell population is in stationary phase. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of menadione that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: cell lysis during mating

value.value: An inviable phenotype observed during mating in which a cell lyses, i.e. the plasma membrane ruptures and cytoplasm is lost, during the process of cell fusion that occurs during mating. Note that in fission yeast cell lysis, the integrity of the cell wall is also compromised.

label.value: normal protein localization to site of mechanical stress

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein at a site of mechanical stress on the cell surface is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished protein localization to site of mechanical stress

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein does not localize to, and is therefore absent from, a site of mechanical stress on the cell surface where it is normally found.

label.value: normal reactive oxygen species level during stationary phase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell that is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during stationary phase.

label.value: dynamic microtubule minus ends in interphase bundles

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton phenotype observed during mitotic interphase in which the microtubule minus ends are dynamic (they alternate between growth and shrinkage phases).

label.value: mitotic spindle collapse during anaphase B elongation with progressive spindle pole congression

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a mitotic spindle assembles and begins to elongate, but collapses during anaphase B, with the collapse being followed by the spindle poles congressing together. In some cases, this is known to be driven by depolymerisation of microtubules part of a merotelic attachment (PMID:19948483).

label.value: increased duration of cytoplasmic microtubule growth events during mitotic interphase

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed during mitotic interphase in which the duration of cytoplasmic microtubule growth events is longer.

label.value: abnormal interphase mitotic telomere clustering during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which telomere clustering is abnormal. Telomere clustering gathers telomeres during or prior to tethering to the nuclear periphery during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: decreased RNA-dependent RNA polymerase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of RNA-dependent RNA polymerase activity is decreased.

label.value: abolished siRNA loading onto RITS complex

value.value: An RNA localization phenotype where the loading of siRNAs onto the RITs complex is abolished.
